INDICATOR_NAME: Prevalence of anemia among children (% of children under 5)
SOURCE_NOTE: Prevalence of anemia, children under age 5, is the percentage of children under age 5 whose hemoglobin level is less than 110 grams per liter at sea level.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION: World Health Organization, Global Health Observatory Data Repository/World Health Statistics (http://apps.who.int/gho/data/node.main.1?lang=en).
